Design System Guidelines



Do not create one-off UI elements for each page



    Reuse and extend existing components instead of redesigning them



    Build a consistent design system:

        Define base components (Button, Card, Input, Section)

        Reuse them across the app with variations

        Maintain consistent spacing, typography, maintain maxwidth/consistent padding to sections and its elements across the entire site and color usage

    Avoid generic or “AI-generated looking” UI patterns

    Prefer intentional, minimal, and structured layouts



    Every design decision should feel:

        purposeful

        consistent

        visually balanced

    Do not introduce new styles randomly

    Extend existing styles instead of creating new ones



Component Design Rules



    Before creating a new component, check if an existing one can be reused



    Components should be:

        composable

        reusable

        scalable

    Avoid inline styling for one-off designs

    Keep styling centralized and consistent



Visual Quality Principles



    Prioritize clarity over decoration

    Use whitespace intentionally

    Maintain strong visual hierarchy (headings, sections, spacing)

    Animations should enhance experience, not distract

    Avoid excessive effects unless explicitly required



Design Goal



The UI should feel:



    crafted, not generated

    consistent, not random

    simple, but high quality
